    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Rituals surrounding the exit from a locale or building. May involve burnt offerings, pit offerings, and broken pottery or ornaments. Examples are in pre-Columbian cultures where it was believed that living spirits inhabit inanimate objects, and that damaging or destroying the object can release the spirit.</Note_Text>
